    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-03T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-03T22:00:00-05:00" n="409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1515: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-04T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 4, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 4—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. Tientsin’s 88, May 3, 4 p.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d409fn6">Not printed.</note>
                    Unless Department perceives objection thereto, I propose to inform Tientsin that
                    Embassy perceives no objection to American owners of property in Tientsin
                    Consular District informing local authorities of status of their titles to
                    property through the Consul General. It is my opinion that Consulate General
                    should notify American citizens that payment of taxes on this property should be
                    made under protest.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping and Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
